Just "\nContext:\n\n\n[add a header comment to tests/network/sshlib\nBen Franksen <ben.franksen@online.de>**20201227154026\n Ignore-this: 2db2e03a13a013281fba51dfd405a2c946144cc9f300a00257da7d56c3cb10fca94c144527c27e0e\n] \n\n[fix errors in zsh completions, add comments\nBen Franksen <ben.franksen@online.de>**20201225100736\n Ignore-this: 128464a1a50359ecff5ba64993d523f6eb8b0e23e8d3c3d4a1b3910272e4de5dda9b6eb68d4adc6d\n \n This fixes a stupid cut-and-paste error where I used x instead of words.\n Also, replacing the first option arg works only if the is an option arg in\n the first place, we need to properly insert --list-options.\n] \n\n[zsh completion: improve the get/clone case\nBen Franksen <ben.franksen@online.de>**20201223162359\n Ignore-this: 50321e24c2b6217277682d19c7e229c1fd1417007a3edd4d0bab0d8167f2505c93c39ee418c6973\n \n Moving the special case for get/clone down into the catch-all case for the\n current word allows it to complete options and local paths.\n] \n\n[zsh completion: use '--list-options' before any other option\nBen Franksen <ben.franksen@online.de>**20201223161522\n Ignore-this: b114faf220c2e8b9cf37c5f823dd8754ace003509d68d08571f68c8a4d189e8c3ac0ac19d866589e\n \n See the corresponding change in the bash completion for details.\n] \n\n[bash_completion: use '--list-options' before any other option\nGian Piero Carrubba <gpiero@rm-rf.it>**20201222114505\n Ignore-this: 3846b35e4c2bfe4e2af2fb5d9120e8686232309864ccf602dd32ad4b34d498f64c81f8beebb0fb1f\n \n This is so to avoid that, e.g.:\n \n $ darcs record -m <Tab><Tab>\n \n results in a patch named '--list-options' being recorded.\n] \n\n[fix: rollback erroneous parts of \"improve cache utilization\"\nBen Franksen <ben.franksen@online.de>**20201223114914\n Ignore-this: bd145a529ea8dcee2da6f771c4dc716769452c7b4a2284aec5edf3293bc3b418f5070d84f76d4318\n \n These changes don't have anything to do with what the patch claims to do\n (and otherwise indeed does). Furthermore, they can lead to unnecessary file\n download, which can make a cloning a local repo extremely slow.\n] \n\n[unrevert: make naming more consistent with D.R.Unrevert and with other commands\nBen Franksen <ben.franksen@online.de>**20201222103143\n Ignore-this: 4cf17ec2fb0a6b5602c3be659f605df8fbf85512d5cea7c24e638adc9454707bf72f1fc1e45f1c70\n] \n\n[revert: make naming more consistent with D.R.Unrevert and with other commands\nBen Franksen <ben.franksen@online.de>**20201222100918\n Ignore-this: 71ba3eb57490c67b6468aef1da6228b13fe5c78c3278c24218292208e5f252b60d2b2f11dfeb32b7\n] \n\n[use promptYorn when asking whether to execute hook\nBen Franksen <ben.franksen@online.de>**20201221205455\n Ignore-this: 9717b654ab039fc52287c43f9f7407751731063fbe5b560b2066a47f077dab9c58dbe78cbf4afa35\n] \n\n[move Hook(s)Config from D.R.Flags to D.UI.Options.All\nBen Franksen <ben.franksen@online.de>**20201221204552\n Ignore-this: 833f56f04bb68a67adb4e9e6e1af1b6ff151854deeec349f15bc9a9de9f2d557f3a8760a359d0343\n] \n\n[reduce code duplication in Darcs.UI.RunHook\nBen Franksen <ben.franksen@online.de>**20201221203724\n Ignore-this: 149f4e24d6fc284077e4ea8c01eefa8072f5f206e7dbb48abd1ca033cd1e519fd000988b6738b34a\n] \n\n[move remainder of D.R.Test to D.UI.RunHook\nBen Franksen <ben.franksen@online.de>**20201221203510\n Ignore-this: d70bb5c6becf35737e550131ef058e7baef0d2f8ed8d588094a742b037026a441741b3b34fe06e66\n] \n\n[inline runTest into getTest and move to UI layer\nBen Franksen <ben.franksen@online.de>**20201221201403\n Ignore-this: afef0d9e3558941f1422c02a697b9758709e09346d41ecd82a6ea523befb6d9ec01b9ac26194da8\n] \n\n[refactor testing of the tentative pristine\nBen Franksen <ben.franksen@online.de>**20201105111940\n Ignore-this: f9272f165e668777a2e0c5be9d292b01f94c1c9d47897717822ba1e26be69048d27612a12c4a3e72\n] \n\n[support --leave-test-dir for all commands that support --test\nBen Franksen <ben.franksen@online.de>**20201105130845\n Ignore-this: a22dfbc912fc2aa2de300316729167839631018a8ff266562966687c80ad138650de94e98309d659\n] \n\n[bugfix: --leave-test-dir should be off by default\nBen Franksen <ben.franksen@online.de>**20201105125044\n Ignore-this: 76d2ef56f7dc3761f38341f7a5d1accf61cac86f9df4b72f466be808afa700109622955730fd6ede\n] \n\n[record command: clean up import lists\nBen Franksen <ben.franksen@online.de>**20201103171036\n Ignore-this: b40c3b56a5bc42d199c161fbdb2ca95226a8b360ae3f795714dbc1112e092b142759ed30cd93f103\n] \n\n[amend and record commands: back to using [DarcsFlag]\nBen Franksen <ben.franksen@online.de>**20201103164644\n Ignore-this: a22a3637d68bba1ba1a21473b4c6ece671aedec1942f35f37937a4c586d5c02f1284930b1a93f827\n \n Introducing configuration for these commands was done as an experiment and\n my conclusion is that it has failed. Haskell's records are just not flexible\n enough to be useful here.\n] \n\n[unify diffing options\nBen Franksen <ben.franksen@online.de>**20201102084906\n Ignore-this: 32c72f40a039dec4b1cefb5fe752d9e3173af9400fd36a625c6ffe5334fd25bfd5f121b9ba0fe87\n \n This lets us treat all options that influence how we determine tree\n differences into a single data type, simplifying type signatures and call\n sites. The ScanKnown repo flag is removed, instead we add a third variant to\n LookForAdds.\n] \n\n[add missing options to some optimize commands\nBen Franksen <ben.franksen@online.de>**20201109192420\n Ignore-this: 37879f2dec790e0bb6e3df63bf2a08be2b8971109608533e2a273865753a543b6dff2e6a76af02fd\n] \n\n[rollback: simplify by inlining undoItNow\nBen Franksen <ben.franksen@online.de>**20201026081046\n Ignore-this: 3f92274700e2fffdbab349c3b88818ea1674987626db0dea162de2b81fba3989e18b790d6f37b5e2\n] \n\n[cleanup import lists in Darcs.Repository.ApplyPatches\nBen Franksen <ben.franksen@online.de>**20201124082621\n Ignore-this: 18c05a87dd80c8452a6b0327a7d868f9de3c993495f7295d7f375273063c4892ff7611d3f20a449a\n] \n\n[remove Darcs.Patch.ApplyPatches\nBen Franksen <ben.franksen@online.de>**20201124082029\n Ignore-this: da69249064f4f79e7755eebae6f73e47d575fe6a9b96f41970d1760542669f8f4753404d98efa17f\n] \n\n[minor refactor in D.UI.ApplyPatches\nBen Franksen <ben.franksen@online.de>**20201105094020\n Ignore-this: 345dc2a2d7d3f6453037474706fb7607f8a25c72c269d91e054f5b77591c463e91e14ba132dfe144\n] \n\n[factor extraction of option components into withStdOpts\nBen Franksen <ben.franksen@online.de>**20201025180815\n Ignore-this: c22992dbce3f55efeda3cb66842591a74889430f27ef5e835717e4235edef6082192e5dbf6ae802b\n \n This saves lots of boilerplate in command definitions.\n] \n\n[move stuff from Darcs.UI.Commands.Util.Tree to Darcs.Util.Tree\nBen Franksen <ben.franksen@online.de>**20201221135110\n Ignore-this: 839dacfab2b2bd83f9ac885625bb69e7494c0680f0d877aec920a7df7c4be78c56099739dcc236f\n] \n\n[rename Darcs.Util.Tree.isSub to isDir\nBen Franksen <ben.franksen@online.de>**20201221133113\n Ignore-this: 1c54b42cdb737bca15ff38fe354f76b3665a8a66156ae300127dd3d5ee89d804d34c6806b01eb0bd\n] \n\n[further simplify Darcs.UI.Commands.Util.Tree\nBen Franksen <ben.franksen@online.de>**20201221132431\n Ignore-this: 7c3b1c3a3638f05c1a7f4f5bbd3d9ff53dc5eee2063d971b9513854df265348d88318a993145208\n \n Use of the TreeMonad here is overkill and can be avoided by adding a simple\n monadic variant of Darcs.Util.Tree.find expands Stubs on the way. Also\n export isSub from Darcs.Util.Tree for convenience.\n] \n\n[simplify TreeMonad by removing its \"current working directory\" emulation\nBen Franksen <ben.franksen@online.de>**20201221124919\n Ignore-this: 6a862703b262a0aa82637dac65b92fb1224c4f482289b3d087a73cf6e27c11b95e3772b8de68f934\n \n Darcs suffers enough from cwd issues in the IO monad. Adding to that by\n emulating a \"current working directory\" as ambient state in the TreeMonad\n was a bad idea from the start. Fortunately the only place where this\n misfeature was used is in the implementation of treeHasAnycase. The new\n implementation of that procedure is both safer and easier to understand.\n] \n\n[general cleanup of D.U.Tree.Monad\nBen Franksen <ben.franksen@online.de>**20200717174840\n Ignore-this: 6ee1b44ffb0fb971cbf9999010c4ef0dc51bf3cc834ac6a0194e4b8eb955bedf984c2e33a4f7d260\n \n This makes a small API change: initialState is no longer exported, instead\n runTreeMonad gets passed the ingredients directly. The main internal change\n is that the updateHash and update procedures have been moved from the\n TreeState to the reader part of the monad, for which there is now a new data\n type TreeEnv. Otherwise this cleans up and documents the export list and\n many of the haddocks, and moves things around a bit.\n] \n\n[cleanup D.U.Tree.Monad: remove classes TreeRO and TreeRW\nBen Franksen <ben.franksen@online.de>**20200717173733\n Ignore-this: 54fd1d4517534debaee420a2766bd54a2db469444cbcf0cf632a96572146534fdc2384d976fba22e\n \n This merely turns the former methods into plain overloaded functions.\n] \n\n[improve cache utilization\nBen Franksen <ben.franksen@online.de>**20201109144750\n Ignore-this: f38c7a912e1998a58dc4b31e31512ac7122bf1268bde6a8cac379792983d2bd893f895e65007274\n \n This adds additional (hard) links between cache locations:\n - create links not only in Directory caches, but in all Writable caches\n - add links when we write a hashed file (was marked as TODO in the sources)\n \n We have to add the --no-cache option in a few test scripts because darcs\n commands are now less likely to fail when we use the cache.\n \n The deeper reason behind this is that it will allow us to use the cache for\n all accesses to hashed pristine files.\n] \n\n[minor cleanups in Darcs.Util.Cache (type signatures, debug messages, etc)\nBen Franksen <ben.franksen@online.de>**20201221100930\n Ignore-this: e539433a5b8d7c8e12d25dfaa49ce44b2ea0c6be0ab07cc15f6cbce8bbfbe4fcb4fbb381275167ca\n] \n\n[clean up import lists in Darcs.Util.Cache\nBen Franksen <ben.franksen@online.de>**20201108091952\n Ignore-this: 3bce241918bb02606e970f6160acad8d88418a681f2933b2ee3f8d6abb19d5a78a87d57d6eef32f4\n] \n\n[move Darcs.Repository.Cache to Darcs.Util.Cache\nBen Franksen <ben.franksen@online.de>**20201108090907\n Ignore-this: 2ab6a53980108adb3fd93013d86a0f73a5bae8322bb1607dce2171e5572ec4da834c36d63d91d1e8\n \n The rationale for this move is that Darcs.Util.Tree.Hashed should be able to\n make use of caches which it previously could not.\n] \n\n[rename last parameter of fetchFileUsingCachePrivate\nBen Franksen <ben.franksen@online.de>**20201109130716\n Ignore-this: 817e11684bae107fcb441bbf6030525cdb622b6897947e841e961ef44ba1e8c295c554aba1886613\n] \n\n[harness: add --cache=[yn] as another column to test script matrix\nBen Franksen <ben.franksen@online.de>**20201110161937\n Ignore-this: 1053dfa8b1b5f2465d3c106a1c4d51b98cb4c2c0c37ba105bb16d7ea3227dce86fed01fc6193a547\n \n This means we can now run shell tests with ALL no-cache as default. This is\n useful in order to check that we don't accidentally rely on the global cache\n for correctness.\n] \n\n[improve haddocks for class PrimSift\nBen Franksen <ben.franksen@online.de>**20201105075330\n Ignore-this: 9f417b8eb485cc41a425effe403fdc72fde4b4051dbde8a1b8507e218d9fd69fb1787f4ec26efe34\n] \n\n[remove Darcs.Util.Printer.Color.debugDoc\nBen Franksen <ben.franksen@online.de>**20201103063249\n Ignore-this: 90f8f7d934e2cafaf1e6f5ed26fe38a1bb35bfdc65b8e4c49f791e300204f6702aff5b87b95caa67\n \n Using color in debug messages is bad. When you redirect stderr to a file it\n will be garbled with escape sequences; similar when piping to grep and so on.\n] \n\n[Darcs.Repository.Job: use Dict to pass dictionaries\nBen Franksen <ben.franksen@online.de>**20201103064250\n Ignore-this: 515973c03aa5e3956bf2361db94d0b291308a1b76e2b11130912b170b6ea715d019420ad06792ecd\n] \n\n[reformat overlong lines in D.T.Patch.Arbitrary.RepoPatchV2\nBen Franksen <ben.franksen@online.de>**20201103063955\n Ignore-this: f1861a853b8b2e645c0f3f3f910c7f1e61d7c323352c890d2dc7347c409945ac7438ed9cfab2a328\n] \n\n[throw out unneeded stuff from win32/System/Posix/IO.hsc\nBen Franksen <ben.franksen@online.de>**20201031105300\n Ignore-this: eedf9a6154d778876c421e9f2f885465031090e10738de71213bdb8f37d4524807ecbf7f2f03a3e3\n] \n\n[add a few debug messages to D.R.State\nBen Franksen <ben.franksen@online.de>**20201030080102\n Ignore-this: 36577274fabfebe1819d7c822c8f441df98bde98ce53edb817e4fcd01641d8f7a0f6a0fa506cc51b\n] \n\n[minor refactor in D.R.State.filteredWorking\nBen Franksen <ben.franksen@online.de>**20201027235543\n Ignore-this: 8ec8158f2d49695eac70b7d06b3c2f0b0a69ba0c119faf8502fa65d144895306003d0aac28facc42\n] \n\n[Darcs.Util.Tree: implement overlay in applicative style\nBen Franksen <ben.franksen@online.de>**20201026190532\n Ignore-this: f35409ec96f2101b7d6f5226dca12ff3a6a64e720415bb0f4fff95090bca140db40f9dff25276717\n \n I find this code now a lot easier to understand.\n] \n\n[remove redundant call to siftForPending in finalizePending\nBen Franksen <ben.franksen@online.de>**20201026100423\n Ignore-this: 5afb1366dd9eb86812e86da4efc8d3084eaba5e1c15969f6a96c87db96762db7ba252e01002f34df\n \n Sifting is done by makeNewPending anyway.\n] \n\n[D.R.State: build w/o warning with TEST_INDEX=1\nBen Franksen <ben.franksen@online.de>**20201030080226\n Ignore-this: 946504ef81f636b7843b76c34ea6a89c339d1638aa27b1d83856647e36ebaf4292ce595282ea539b\n] \n\n[remove invalidateIndex\nBen Franksen <ben.franksen@online.de>**20201030085308\n Ignore-this: 3c7daf4a7c17ddedad523c00a49cf74eb7c2a2ed567045f66fc9219a67449b46a9f13a8dd716baff\n \n Instead of creating _darcs/index_invalid we now directly call updateIndex\n where necessary. This was already done in finalizeRepositoryChanges (and\n also in the add and move commands) in order to support --look-for-moves\n which requires an up-to-date index. This is now handled uniformly by adding\n a call to updateIndex inside addToPending and addPendingDiffToPending, which\n are the two functions called by commands that modify only the pending patch\n and not any recorded patches and thus do not currently call\n finalizeRepositoryChanges. The UI layer no longer needs to concern itself\n with the index at all (other than passing down the value of the useIndex\n option).\n \n For compatibility we still check if _darcs/index_invalid exists and\n re-create the index in that case.\n] \n\n[fix haddocks for D.U.Index.updateItem\nBen Franksen <ben.franksen@online.de>**20201028075420\n Ignore-this: eeaa38ebe50545ea8d02fd5e5063920a7ee4d1205aa1a921d78675fd8c24687067c524467b065c2a\n] \n\n[index: use iPath instead of realPath\nBen Franksen <ben.franksen@online.de>**20201104075251\n Ignore-this: b5ee9ed31440568c2c0b25617dbd641059835bcfe1587c85ec3a4f49ba9520f693a7a173bf6b38a6\n \n This is more consistent and perhaps a bit faster.\n] \n\n[index: add progress reports when \"reading\" (actually updating) the index\nBen Franksen <ben.franksen@online.de>**20201104075948\n Ignore-this: 18d6b84a8f24b7273a6caafb477b8b4101beed834ebfaf4d42e3cff7afc7f727e5a8665de3ecac91\n \n Indeed reading the index involves updating items: file size, timestamp, file\n ID, and content hash are updated in case they aren't properly indexed yet.\n This can take quite some time if the index is generated for the first time\n or there are lots of changes in the working tree.\n] \n\n[index: make readDir/readFile local to readItem\nBen Franksen <ben.franksen@online.de>**20201104074929\n Ignore-this: b0ef74b7fb41c71efa95b351da293103a5274a0eb0704ab66332c404ccd24e5c76d5513b59ad34e2\n] \n\n[use file IDs from unix-compat\nBen Franksen <ben.franksen@online.de>**20201028225015\n Ignore-this: ba67f0e3f259479193eb3f716395234b4f8b3e58f7f22b04f0fed5b1d23d03ebc85e561442f38858\n \n The Windows specific functionality in the index code to get at the Win32\n equivalent to Unix inode numbers is covered by the unix-compat package since\n version 0.4.1.3. This avoids unnecessary extra calls to createFile.\n] \n\n[minor refactor in D.Util.Index.readDir\nBen Franksen <ben.franksen@online.de>**20201027235316\n Ignore-this: 68ccf91cf63fae9c50e338622db9227218db699a039b519719ee684abc0f09bb523aef2efed484b9\n] \n\n[index: remove unnecessary conversions\nBen Franksen <ben.franksen@online.de>**20201029094232\n Ignore-this: 344900e537aca5fcc08a8a724553e044d16baf860b3dabd77edb92a6d61800f57c555d3eb4624488\n] \n\n[index: update a few comments\nBen Franksen <ben.franksen@online.de>**20201104102437\n Ignore-this: c4788c64d427ce8ca890d7df8ef1785aac8f404ab15c75a5e4564ace3baa198409b85b23d3f45c27\n] \n\n[add some debug messages (index, patch index)\nBen Franksen <ben.franksen@online.de>**20201102171615\n Ignore-this: 38f90cd4cb8dc790bdb603004c617a858ae6c91ea531326981b59ee50cbd0cf5cd11ced927bcfc0c\n] \n\n[simplify the logic that handles existence and validity of the index\nBen Franksen <ben.franksen@online.de>**20201029140141\n Ignore-this: 5e281f0f13f9177a1a70c84ed7f3408119eeb1f064cb90aa3bd50af0ebb8674cae5900f77cc8534f\n] \n\n[rename D.Util.Index.readIndex to openIndex\nBen Franksen <ben.franksen@online.de>**20201027233536\n Ignore-this: ce870e8084a9413c175c62c9065d33c66ebb8b43a522987108ed3cb1650020799beb32b4ab2abd31\n \n This is a more fitting name since this function merely creates a cursor for\n the index without actually reading anything interesting (besides the magic\n word). It also resolves the last name conflict in D.R.State which means we\n can now import D.Util.Index unqualified.\n] \n\n[Darcs.Util.Index: rename updateIndex to treeFromIndex\nBen Franksen <ben.franksen@online.de>**20201026173310\n Ignore-this: 19598868d0d26672147e5b17b8fadd651ad90ca7af4ccf71be501aafa3451bfccfc74b70905f50d2\n \n This function does not update the index, it merely creates a Tree out of an\n Index. This also avoids the name collision with the function from\n Darcs.Repository.State which does update the index. Also add haddocks and\n rename a local variable that denotes a tree, not an index.\n] \n\n[darcs check: add a warning when we cannot access the index\nBen Franksen <ben.franksen@online.de>**20201030103855\n Ignore-this: 4c5b45504824df995eb90b546a1eb56e2aa34cdc2ae129b4df78a12b8e015a51582076db0a91b834\n \n This was already done for all other \"read-only\" commands.\n] \n\n[show index: show everything, not just hash, id, and path\nBen Franksen <ben.franksen@online.de>**20201030095336\n Ignore-this: ffdabbdf0bf29c0ee064e78cb5ed0a4a3e13d58595669d7ffd45b4473a7516df8a8a9afb07e2d9dc\n] \n\n[index: in the docs, replace \"line\" with \"Item\", clarify size/alignment\nBen Franksen <ben.franksen@online.de>**20201029100739\n Ignore-this: 71d0bb4730782a801ca4a6741c47b6e4d85e67c1152b815aee9e6b11ae7f548e521ed053b47c1c0b\n] \n\n[index: use realPath instead of anchorPath \"\"\nBen Franksen <ben.franksen@online.de>**20201029081535\n Ignore-this: 867958a2261b4b44a28fb99d7b73461cd06f0068fddf2ee4d8128be8e0f2b695baf415152babb1a4\n] \n\n[index: move update of fileid out of createItem\nBen Franksen <ben.franksen@online.de>**20201029081145\n Ignore-this: 57ad500386b60dc03f58a83d877154a254ff3668813ba68d4051f2245144a65825e7fa0ef8bddfbe\n \n This is a preparation for a later refactor.\n] \n\n[index: re-use getFileStatus for getFileID' (Posix)\nBen Franksen <ben.franksen@online.de>**20201029075933\n Ignore-this: e977152e45278a08e184a7d1d4d2e04947c2677671c38fb6168b1337dfa7ab1d69905e43f6b34aba\n] \n\n[avoid useless CPP in D.U.Index and D.R.State\nBen Franksen <ben.franksen@online.de>**20201027232018\n Ignore-this: 73537921ac1721450cad27e1c8931a1d32d539baea5017e15fca1e67a218b792d1d28cb0472cdfd9\n \n We can use the same action (renameFile instead of removeFile) for both\n Windows and Posix. The point here is that the index may still be open via an\n mmapped ForeignPtr, so removing it is not portable, but renaming it should\n work on all systems.\n] \n\n[make test for remote darcs log a bit faster\nBen Franksen <ben.franksen@online.de>**20201110124018\n Ignore-this: b538187e1033b81be06757382063543049d300412b41d85a4d04fadecf8dff11d5e1961ed64fd803\n] \n\n[tests/EXAMPLE.sh: explain and follow best practices\nBen Franksen <ben.franksen@online.de>**2020111