5335c4b1138c45afcf601a675c7551014e893b496c19090e03a6498e9857919cf83b1ccc18\n] \n\n[enable use of the index in the test suite by default\nBen Franksen <ben.franksen@online.de>**20201030141233\n Ignore-this: a34802f507e57b7222fc63ed4064510c1d7d004467d5a86aa1479018faaf4809cb0fc6546431b12a\n \n This also adapts test scripts that assumed the former default in order to\n test the right thing. We now pass --ignore-times (or its opposite)\n explicitly instead.\n] \n\n[harness: add flag to test with or without the index\nBen Franksen <ben.franksen@online.de>**20201028095230\n Ignore-this: 26397cefbb94b817414fb7e02247dbca6da010d57b69b42e38cb34db23f2bd2e11527c370eacfa61\n] \n\n[index: use high resolution timestamps\nBen Franksen <ben.franksen@online.de>**20201027234549\n Ignore-this: b91248ff1247519644c1f834adfe07d06cf4614aec87df91b4cbcc4313d7b8d08a1a1ca16e7696a1\n \n This requires building against a patched unix-compat, since the pull request\n is still pending. Tests scripts where sleep calls were inserted or\n --ignore-times was explicitly passed in order to work around low timestamp\n resolutions have been adapted accordingly. In the network tests I have kept\n the explicit --ignore-times when executing the remote darcs, because this\n may be a version of darcs different from the one under test.\n] \n\n[Darcs.Util.Index: fix a few minor errors in comments\nBen Franksen <ben.franksen@online.de>**20201026174645\n Ignore-this: 4f147c7e2c367028a42606c36bce535070b4e298e55e9cce0cc486a2166daabd61a50513ff043443\n] \n\n[remove extraneous setting of --ignore-times in test scripts\nBen Franksen <ben.franksen@online.de>**20201025060715\n Ignore-this: 9ba7495b6266d70457f3bb50ac08abd4a2194b33adb2c9859eb02eadfaac07f45ae02d7d231977a3\n] \n\n[make --ignore-times a standard option supported by all commands\nBen Franksen <ben.franksen@online.de>**20201025063626\n Ignore-this: 33d9209da9a88f9d3f5f6a5319eea55890b5dee7e373eb79e361a7a73b8e813b8998830fa9b81a3d\n \n This also fixes all places where we still passed the UseIndex constructor\n directly without considering the option value.\n] \n\n[add tests/list-options.sh\nBen Franksen <ben.franksen@online.de>**20201102122836\n Ignore-this: 86ace49ccae317ad29524502e96a46d095f3e71f1a5fa3014f0ea22235842784fbf834659b626ffc\n] \n\n[move removeFromUnrevertContext to D.R.Unrevert\nBen Franksen <ben.franksen@online.de>**20201219145136\n Ignore-this: 84b34ae587c7f0bd4e1c4852d4d6f2a148b1a84c3d0e62a7d1b6871c34440b1d43b858027834d15d\n] \n\n[simplify removeFromUnrevertContext\nBen Franksen <ben.franksen@online.de>**20201103073735\n Ignore-this: e15affba0c241f043e95d634ecec23933afbc7c12e147f12f4d091ba4a157521a607969799ad7483\n] \n\n[unrevert: use promptYorn instead of askUser\nBen Franksen <ben.franksen@online.de>**20201023161430\n Ignore-this: 6fdf02c89f4d9aacb25cc013758427da87b7ca026e96e356c47666d361a1f24298d4f7eae70af3ce\n] \n\n[move call to readRepo out of writeUnrevert\nBen Franksen <ben.franksen@online.de>**20201023143426\n Ignore-this: bc2f23214bf935e0c9df7fbc8b4af4e6b8289aef3e76ff9405b9c61298163b6d11f6d22353a049bf\n \n This prepares for moving removeFromUnrevertContext from D.R.Hashed to\n D.R.Unrevert. It also makes it utterly clear that unrevert is unsafe: we\n read the repo and then modify the unrevert bundle /after/ it the changes\n have been finalized.\n] \n\n[cleanup imports in Darcs.UI.Commands.Unrevert\nBen Franksen <ben.franksen@online.de>**20201023135933\n Ignore-this: ffbdd701ab0d0abbcbd123b7a6ce3f71b65a406e09ac40bdc41d19e8c6b4ce8faf6f416bf3b4edef\n] \n\n[move writeUnrevert and unrevertPatchBundle to Darcs.Repository.Unrevert\nBen Franksen <ben.franksen@online.de>**20201023134522\n Ignore-this: 472bcd9eb2efb997410e9b52f5872efe3d41c2e7c6d4ea07cbd18ec4373e1d42b5108931d2e3b7b0\n] \n\n[writeUnrevert: remove the 'pending' argument\nBen Franksen <ben.franksen@online.de>**20201023133152\n Ignore-this: e1ab863cb42b102fcd4362b4dd181ddab00c651f54cf055eaf8fc2af7d7fd0e0eebb4d068f1726d0\n \n This is a preparation for moving writeUnrevert to the Repository layer. The\n code we move from writeUnrevert into the command implementation is asking\n the user, so belongs to the UI layer.\n] \n\n[unrevert: rename some local variables\nBen Franksen <ben.franksen@online.de>**20201023133320\n Ignore-this: bca26a57b29e5905e6060870b76c8e7fc7779f237c499f0e4e054b1da90cafc741dc6fc9dbdb2c\n] \n\n[make writeUnrevert take its arguments in a more natural order\nBen Franksen <ben.franksen@online.de>**20201023095051\n Ignore-this: c60f26bc98095a595caf704586a4a145ae8591d753b69142637dd0ca46803e808bd08d2a68d22a78\n] \n\n[adapt regex to ignore build directory in our boringfile\nBen Franksen <ben.franksen@online.de>**20201219082646\n Ignore-this: 64be87827098db511cd8867f61e139de88a15d2907c72de75951a6ad328670fff1f705bc21e4704c\n] \n\n[default boring: replace ($|/) with /\nBen Franksen <ben.franksen@online.de>**20201219223245\n Ignore-this: 90bd63dd5bae4812b6e0303b92fc80dd60049fe6b16d8146fdee9ff4815e99b657227652baee3711\n \n This pattern was used to match a directory or any of its entries\n (recursively) and can now be simplified.\n] \n\n[fix tests/issue2668-*.sh: use /bin/pwd, not pwd, in exit handler\nBen Franksen <ben.franksen@online.de>**20201218120143\n Ignore-this: 7f5a67c117aa7f9e99082013e9a3f23c7a5fa0f4d973b745cb246ecb4f802b7865497b5864d1366b\n \n Otherwise this test fails on Windows in the github ci.\n] \n\n[tests/network/clone-http-packed-detect.sh: fix spurious failures on MacOS\nBen Franksen <ben.franksen@online.de>**20201218120749\n Ignore-this: 33ee55c51dce6935cfa1ed5b4fde85ac83e155c32e4bc003c9ce24520b15eb54136e921820cb7e0f\n] \n\n[prospective fix in tests/network/httplib: && and || have the same precedence in bash\nBen Franksen <ben.franksen@online.de>**20201218120335\n Ignore-this: 6468ed6dd03664cc57bfde458abfa3dcef38795c8e01bcb8264d3afdb87a77b4ff224283f6bb783a\n \n I haven't seen any failures caused by this which is probably because the\n first term (test -e...) never fails if the http server was successfully\n started. Still, logically the code is now more correct.\n] \n\n[append slashes to dirs before matching against boring regexps\nBen Franksen <ben.franksen@online.de>**20201217164903\n Ignore-this: 9d56e66051c2288e69c3120a1c6af6325fa9236f17af6d8cd8150fd251c4c75bab7cdb2849f1ef2d\n \n This resolves the first (minor) part of issue2669 where adding directories\n named 'core' and 'tags' fails due to the default boring file. It also\n requires a small change in one of the test scripts, where we want to ignore\n a particular directory.\n] \n\n[refactor: use isBoring and realPath in D.R.State\nBen Franksen <ben.franksen@online.de>**20201217111933\n Ignore-this: 32544098fd575cec3d7b615bd5d3f895e78a0c5d8cfa6c35ed6b96d3dbe38714da9f77f6dffea0bc\n] \n\n[stack.yaml: add alternative resolvers with work-arounds\nBen Franksen <ben.franksen@online.de>**20201204062327\n Ignore-this: e1c9ab8b9a1e103dafcfa6e58f9b6c24af713a9fa77bd922a810adb786f02141d5085fcaf142067e\n] \n\n[remove the class CharLike from Darcs.Util.Path\nBen Franksen <ben.franksen@online.de>**20201218090456\n Ignore-this: 3fea8423071f42aa78ac42f611972dc84ef8e8d44c7c009008dbd05c99df412f00c1d45757d92f9\n \n We can define instances for FilePath directly, which is simpler and less\n obscure.\n] \n\n[resolve issue2670: convert \".\" to absolute path when creating a repo\nBen Franksen <ben.franksen@online.de>**20201218090331\n Ignore-this: b0134c1fa3d705bd3c90fa0b0c1b1ef272609d9d197127f0169d6d4e22833de5f61bb69bb7085480\n \n Note that this is what we also do in Darcs.Repository.Identify.\n] \n\n[add test for issue2668 (both parts)\nBen Franksen <ben.franksen@online.de>**20201204061300\n Ignore-this: 24bc30d99efea43054f67ad14559e60b65fbbb23229dd0206b387769b6b2027fe695cab4e39ce6ed\n] \n\n[resolve issue2668: part2\nBen Franksen <ben.franksen@online.de>**20201204064751\n Ignore-this: 178c56824b1140350d65a1812efb558dfdfe7d28c8f1a20a78f306fea79cda54f089f909ad0aa3c7\n \n We have to catch IO errors when calling createOrUpdatePatchIndexDisk as this\n is not an essential failure and we are already past finalizing any other\n changes we made.\n] \n\n[resolve issue2668/part1\nBen Franksen <ben.franksen@online.de>**20201204061240\n Ignore-this: 29322a50f27a46b3a57e84db3d3371dd1578ccde2f02e605ee3234acbe487bfa83a39f2ca6071788\n \n This fixes the problem that causes storing the patch-index to fail if the\n parent of the repodir is read-only.\n] \n\n[resolve issue2667: catch IO errors in seekRepo\nBen Franksen <ben.franksen@online.de>**20201120164610\n Ignore-this: 780a0ccf1e2a6f7712849226a220de5e7aee83d100be0c60bd60a8b8f8a040591711545b278c25cb\n \n When we (recursively) cd \"..\" to determine if we are in a darcs repo, we may\n well hit an IO error, such as permission denied. We now catch such errors,\n emit a warning, and return Nothing (not in a repo).\n] \n\n[tests/lib: add comments to explain special Windows settings\nBen Franksen <ben.franksen@online.de>**20201121160453\n Ignore-this: aaeb1d4c2a063135a7de5e30e2d0a50f007be6d16e756f69765fd9bf22c88b351e02b7f78eb18ae5\n] \n\n[ci: add comments and slightly extend the trigger-ci script\nBen Franksen <ben.franksen@online.de>**20201121154800\n Ignore-this: 6ce828ee632df4be16ba53d46b7b67d2bb1d4b46452e5fcfc79926e93b4f25f5e5f065492d3b698b\n \n The comment explains that what is committed into the git repo is the pending\n unrecorded state, not the recorded state. Also remove the redundant\n --pending flag for darcs show files. Instead, add -A flag to 'git add' in\n order to include pending file removals with the commit.\n] \n\n[ci: reduce tests on Windows to darcs-2 format\nBen Franksen <ben.franksen@online.de>**20201120155812\n Ignore-this: 57866ee15aa04255b744af0327ab51ad6c3156690e2c40cee1b27c86f946d303739c2e0b2abca2a4\n \n Running the shell tests on Windows takes about thrice as long as for Linux\n and macOS, over one hour in total.\n] \n\n[ci: enable running the tests on Windows\nBen Franksen <ben.franksen@online.de>**20201119162154\n Ignore-this: a86c78b8a1ccaec1f40154f17b72c4c1f46fa4baf8206efcec05b480a31ee8fde6692febc9d6a6a2\n] \n\n[tests/printer.sh: disable test for \\r encoding on Windows\nBen Franksen <ben.franksen@online.de>**20201119100616\n Ignore-this: 9834f2c3c9accab3691b69d0d95e4b38e9e7932742e82db177f3134d4e29e59acc01e6717f692b20\n \n This fails for reasons that are still unclear to me.\n] \n\n[tests: remove obsolete setting of DARCS_EDITOR\nBen Franksen <ben.franksen@online.de>**20201116090245\n Ignore-this: 8e4bca995d00a2654aec63fb91f32cf455536de429c593576278505bb810d2cae9e3137ae8283b51\n \n We nowadays have --no-edit-description in the defaults when testing.\n] \n\n[ci: restructure the caching apparatus\nBen Franksen <ben.franksen@online.de>**20201119162036\n Ignore-this: b774c3273ee3ee9cd72804d26bd06bd3c9ce5efc7062ababd32458023c0afb835b44e69bbbc8021b\n] \n\n[ci: use runner.os instead of fiddling with matrix.os\nBen Franksen <ben.franksen@online.de>**20201119161935\n Ignore-this: 32a358dc298d6e2e9c77acee63ff2f036dd1112c9d7b0faafb5dda81464e4d6636020f76eb52efcc\n \n The runner.os gives us the OS class in a simple way.\n] \n\n[ci: add ACTIONS_ALLOW_UNSECURE_COMMANDS\nBen Franksen <ben.franksen@online.de>**20201119161648\n Ignore-this: 2b5e1f1ca9a62dbae7dc906e306df71687b78718a8f90541e3f9f0a5d3408e42718211ff614a26e2\n \n This became necessary because of a change in the github actions. Hopefully\n actions/setup-haskell will be adapted soon so we can take this out again.\n] \n\n[ci: remove --hidesuccesses when running the tests\nBen Franksen <ben.franksen@online.de>**20201119161305\n Ignore-this: 9e8df4b328ae2bfca936a70cb14923f1be385c7a430ca87f57a05b4e0fb98ab6c1fb2a76daf3c2ea\n \n It turned out that when we accidentally invoke MAPI on Windows, the command\n may hang indefinitely. With --hidesuccesses it is hard to detect that\n situation since running the tests on Windows is very slow.\n] \n\n[ci: use ghc-8.8.4, not ghc-8.8.2\nBen Franksen <ben.franksen@online.de>**20201119161234\n Ignore-this: f20295f38cc6eeb25740fa1ad876c8cf478b5aa5f852aa914e492f4a244f94eab2d3eb1454dc5afa\n] \n\n[tests/lib: factor out os_is_windows function\nBen Franksen <ben.franksen@online.de>**20201115210637\n Ignore-this: 712b299ac3a82cbe5d72858f18fb37426159edca6820e2e8640951441c427aee8384bb79358714b9\n] \n\n[tests/lib: include \\r in IFS on Windows\nBen Franksen <ben.franksen@online.de>**20201115222029\n Ignore-this: 968041ece52d0c702b9c776b634a6219a4701c95646d6541f108a59b0f419ddc620a7a57ae684225\n \n This makes several of the tests succeed when I run the CI.\n] \n\n[tests/add_permissions.sh: enable commented parts of the test\nBen Franksen <ben.franksen@online.de>**20201115110445\n Ignore-this: f76aba6923a98f75b91c03c097309a9c115ca1b359c03807f39da03939fba5a66cf2a317930472\n] \n\n[fix tests/send-external.sh so that it works on windows, too\nBen Franksen <ben.franksen@online.de>**20201119100118\n Ignore-this: 9e8c027b68f8b95144d590d3a3520e59fc936aa5b30135f2715c49b4a19c010853578b7b331a5b46\n \n Unfortunately it is not fully clear why invoking the generated script via\n bash does not work on Windows, whereas invoking a Haskell script via runghc\n works.\n] \n\n[more Windows test fixes\nBen Franksen <ben.franksen@online.de>**20201119100445\n Ignore-this: 6a67ce0b1093f179830ea99100ee1c3122bed4283dd1ee2a72d80ce983f5c07bb130452f678ee54e\n] \n\n[add a debug message to execSendmail\nBen Franksen <ben.franksen@online.de>**20201119075357\n Ignore-this: bbeb50246430bd5e6ed26c6df23131b915e091af73e66e9003c691a29d49044887d92ed04c83510b\n] \n\n[clean up some of the email sending mess\nBen Franksen <ben.franksen@online.de>**20201116083542\n Ignore-this: a9c5ad49bc33a0a17a1608cc0ef0410bfd2f266f4518aa968236f990c5f53bc9a330f34348b30c25\n \n Searching for a sendmail command in paths like /sbin makes sense only on\n Unix-like systems. This code is now guarded behind #ifndef WIN32. Since we\n always use MAPI on Windows, unless a sendmail-command is specified via the\n option or the SENDMAIL environment, I have replaced HAVE_MAPI with WIN32\n enerywhere. Furthermore, the send command itself no longer has #ifdefs, as\n we pull the check for early failure into D.UI.External as (Os-independent)\n checkDefaultSendmail, adding a TODO comment that this should be improved (on\n Windows) to check whether using MAPI has a chance to succeed.\n] \n\n[remove unused function resendEmail\nBen Franksen <ben.franksen@online.de>**20201117091605\n Ignore-this: 4cbf0516e1afbae8e74ab534077741843f6097266ffa8fb444d90cafec632f9d893810fa4fb47f1e\n] \n\n[ci: re-configure git globally on windows\nBen Franksen <ben.franksen@online.de>**20201115223428\n Ignore-this: 1ae5a7db209574d7bbd15b8b140fcc95c556546754d7c0854bd6b74e473fa14638a39253a9584ff9\n \n This must be done to prevent our test data from being checked out with\n additional CRs.\n] \n\n[fix broken tests/issue1101.sh\nBen Franksen <ben.franksen@online.de>**20201115222352\n Ignore-this: 53ef54ffdd1843b8a04de47c615eb31123fa72ba591658a65814d9290c9b24e83fce6c63660cd9e3\n] \n\n[tests: compare paths in a more portable fashion\nBen Franksen <ben.franksen@online.de>**20201115221728\n Ignore-this: 908a3961555c4f114962ec6c04d2eed5dfa354784c06554e57b81b85fa4dc3248b6b48aa316774d9\n \n This replaces the grep pattern '/filename$' with uses of test and basename,\n which has a better chance of succeeding on Windows.\n] \n\n[tests: simplify comparing patch bundles\nBen Franksen <ben.franksen@online.de>**20201115041039\n Ignore-this: bebb1bb77d4f90dd93d3820aaa29ad130b8dd27eefa64f603d7cc4b4f4a3dab76e1087600bbbc294\n] \n\n[tests: more of the usual test repo removal fixes\nBen Franksen <ben.franksen@online.de>**20201115210552\n Ignore-this: 97ede33c3ee76ca10c8cf057f89c6b591f8682cd30e2f93f7d1274c58bd36b2a85ac1ad24e2435c1\n] \n\n[ci: include pending files in the git commit\nBen Franksen <ben.franksen@online.de>**20201115205030\n Ignore-this: d211ae8256107cf21df0b6dce3ff6a91ee55b8af97e10b9208a3692e74ff834e6fbf7db3e0062418\n] \n\n[convert darcs-2: more advice and a friendlier, shorter confirmation prompt\nSimon Michael <simon@joyful.com>**20201120221947\n Ignore-this: e69feb13e6843da1bba76efbc95082ec1bfb68311ddafb49b63c1645b3657c54d7459f3c091e81a\n] \n\n[rollback \"relax lower bound for base16-bytestring\"\nBen Franksen <ben.franksen@online.de>**20201118160140\n Ignore-this: d3862407a9e85bdddde168acc8f65b39fea36662a164452a0ed6fd3d1eead06c41ff68e395d5173b\n \n This is no longer needed when adding base16-bytestring as an extra-deps\n entry in the stack config.\n] \n\n[upgrade stack resolver to 16.22, add base16-bytestring to extra-deps\nBen Franksen <ben.franksen@online.de>**20201118154357\n Ignore-this: 45fb098bdc398ea0666f197ef911ab392a1677cabb72c9cbdba36fd139bd8e69afa02604bc7c5958\n] \n\n[TAG 2.16.3\nBen Franksen <ben.franksen@online.de>**20201022094642\n Ignore-this: bd76d7e31488721e4a5ce7267115e71c3b68d680c155c75c3dd275d9e54933a607d208fab502a143\n] \n\n[relax lower bound for base16-bytestring\nBen Franksen <ben.franksen@online.de>**20201022083319\n Ignore-this: 35f82d69f748482c7bd2a3b94e77ff8df34d9cb047814024c772b59542e3e8b0dc1ed75c0022bc4a\n \n This requires a bit of CPP hacking but allows to build with stack.\n] \n\n[add a stack.yaml\nBen Franksen <ben.franksen@online.de>**20201022094619\n Ignore-this: 7329409308c4bb29294b5c23b89190bc38a630f780deb04fc3b59878168bbdec2b63ae7cfb73f5b3\n] \n\n[add stack instructions to the README\nBen Franksen <ben.franksen@online.de>**20201022085309\n Ignore-this: c6494cff3e73b519552b95f32502e11e9e562a56c7c08d496013b9079a8ba873d6acb20916b8949b\n] \n\n[ci: remove hashed-store tests\nBen Franksen <ben.franksen@online.de>**20201114174929\n Ignore-this: 65e59063ec31091968abd3a6ef467b43362e067a5c25ca0c80d4cb2c076ba7b90c42179c2cdef678\n \n They fail which is most probably because they aren't re-entrant.\n] \n\n[remove the \"compiled on <timestamp>\" from exact version\nBen Franksen <ben.franksen@online.de>**20201114065931\n Ignore-this: e1054c592f1627673b4196c813c5c3d18c39800aa80832d9005a6a8219bfe5fdbd1a995d885b215d\n \n This information is not of much help and makes it impossible to create darcs\n binaries reproducably. It also causes problems when building in MacOS.\n] \n\n[tests: some portability fixes for MacOS\nBen Franksen <ben.franksen@online.de>**20201114104632\n Ignore-this: d2c5de6b3dd4ee2a5c19db6bdf197281bbeff5871f5b3c44e4646392c2c7cbf36b5d2f74c6ca71f4\n \n Defaulting the directory argument of find to \".\" is is a GNUism and doesn't\n work on MacOS. Similarly, 'wc -l' on MacOS has spaces in its output, the new\n code is simpler and more portable. Also the test command in the MacOS bash\n apparently cannot handle the '!' operator.\n] \n\n[add CI support using github actions\nBen Franksen <ben.franksen@online.de>**20201114170732\n Ignore-this: 31fe9e47eaaaa949452c647f9f3bc86b8f33bfc953438f3176ba8bc8f69b5a96455a2a663eb1de99\n \n For the moment this is manually triggered using ./release/trigger-ci. This\n script takes the basename of the current directory as the git branch name,\n makes sure we are inside a darcs repo, and then creates an automatic commit\n on that branch (creating it if necessary), then force-pushes that branch to\n the github repo, which will trigger the CI run. If a .git does not exist\n yet, it will be created, which means your branch will be reset to this\n snapshot as the first and only version. The configuration of the job to run\n is in .github/workflows/build-and-test.yml. Windows tests are currently\n disable because they run into errors I have no idea how to fix.\n] \n\n[simplify usage of darcs-test\nBen Franksen <ben.franksen@online.de>**20201028091831\n Ignore-this: 7c84560f34a06407c8fc3b5744ddabc981d6000839999d14ef8441fe0d9648b29ff01eb90219758\n \n The UI to select which darcs formats to test, which test suites to run, and\n which diff algorithms to use is changed so that the user now directly\n specifies these sets as strings, rather than having to supply a separate\n flag for each variant. This is much more convenient to use.\n] \n\n[Fix gen-version-info.hs to work in snapshots\nGanesh Sittampalam <ganesh@earth.li>**20201111211803\n Ignore-this: 871ef56dd89222eb69919263e4c15c71d07a9659753a47359c1739157c1be23dbb3e7587736743cb\n \n Commands such as \"darcs test\" just copy the tree without\n _darcs, so we need the build to work in those situations\n without having pre-generated files available.\n] \n\n[add stuff generated by stack to the boringfile\nBen Franksen <ben.franksen@online.de>**20201022090341\n Ignore-this: e6a1176b667526c966459d4c4cc2ff9d0e65a6e09c1760eb6dc9e64315f5bf16426739330414769c\n] \n\n[add changelog entries for 2.16.3\nBen Franksen <ben.franksen@online.de>**20200906113450\n Ignore-this: 85cf39b114eae2da071e1f0d2aaba6cfcc1d82212551d99e6707e0ab8823bb481ea4211332f8ef51\n] \n\n[relax upper bound for conduit to <1.4\nBen Franksen <ben.franksen@online.de>**20201022083558\n Ignore-this: 1248e35931d74034f2acec876fa37f4481e84f253103c5c60e8cae29d1d74cb1c6af287dcd0d6e7c\n] \n\n[adapt README.md to 2.16, plus some restructuring\nBen Franksen <ben.franksen@online.de>**20201021215935\n Ignore-this: 1df7dbc4b7f330af436a69235bfe17d2db1c1417b63b6f0ca6e4a16ad1d51dea12aa2dc67f35c3b0\n] \n\n[bump version to 2.16.3\nBen Franksen <ben.franksen@online.de>**20200906113526\n Ignore-this: ab8dd275dca3da611581aafddadcab34dfc007bedaaf71fa5d06f46a3d38f42804acff8b9acea0e6\n] \n\n[add a cabal.project file\nBen Franksen <ben.franksen@online.de>**20201021124513\n Ignore-this: 1f4ad28f6ab7e542cb318576e49cdc4033c56b1a698da406a697a4eed89a3455329a115d29279690\n \n The cabal-3.2 tool by default scans subdirectories for cabal files. But we\n no longer treat the embedded shelly as a separate cabal package, so for\n cabal-3.2 we want to disable that. While cabal-3.4 changes the default back\n to ./*.cabal, it seems advisable not to rely on the defaults if they prove\n to be volatile.\n] \n\n[Darcs.UI.Flags: reformat some of the code and comments\nBen Franksen <ben.franksen@online.de>**20200720105005\n Ignore-this: 894b1632355a28593b2476991fac3d893a82bac83047da0dac18c203ac1e09b4b90930fd8c44b5d3\n] \n\n[Darcs.UI.Flags: add module haddocks\nBen Franksen <ben.franksen@online.de>**20200720104946\n Ignore-this: 5edb970404f405a818e51ab6a4da8e7de5af91acc690da01b549830c6ef64f2875c739618e1effe7\n] \n\n[add regression test for issue2659\nBen Franksen <ben.franksen@online.de>**20201020092510\n Ignore-this: 89a79b08fa58b153fe6f30e882ff1f03657e470dbedcacab0956d70678428cd96711aba5f2701ad\n] \n\n[tests/record.sh: remove directories before creating them\nBen Franksen <ben.franksen@online.de>**20201020090850\n Ignore-this: afc159e959a50819e3165f18ea956606b241c436af8c95b3e4c90ee645a3fb0764f6db59d1e2e6e5\n] \n\n[tests/record.sh: fix tests for bad patch names\nBen Franksen <ben.franksen@online.de>**20201020085643\n Ignore-this: 6ad082bdbccd9d60f7c57ed00ebec2acd279adee325cb7c50d0f429f348938a0b4f94f29af9c9e9c\n \n It turned out that we do have a test for bad patch names even for the case\n where an editor is invoked, they were just utterly broken i.e. they did not\n test what they claimed to. Using DARCS_EDITOR='cat -n' defeats the purpose\n as this adds line numbers, so the patch name will always be valid. Also, if\n there is nothing to record, the command always fails, regardless of whether\n the patch name is valid or not.\n] \n\n[tests/conflict-fight-failure.sh: skip test if system has no time executable\nBen Franksen <ben.franksen@online.de>**20200928161327\n Ignore-this: 7bf53c02839db8f05f27b2c4f4c03e7afd2ad624dc322342fb26ee2cb2febaa24c3c4a0f9233803f\n] \n\n[harness: add XDG_CACHE_HOME to the env file\nBen Franksen <ben.franksen@online.de>**20200928155444\n Ignore-this: 37a398cde086ba74a1b665796eaa9b227212d23688cb81257d6f5d30cd33ad069834f82975fe318e\n] \n\n[remove an obsolete TODO comment\nBen Franksen <ben.franksen@online.de>**20201019115051\n Ignore-this: 59e55f0a37d55f2fdd7edb32b9d172cb7dc243f04620dd6be361b448e61a3e466f4992a71a62d481\n] \n\n[D.UI.PatchHeader: add \"error\" prefix to bad patch name error messages\nBen Franksen <ben.franksen@online.de>**20201019083044\n Ignore-this: b3d7ead8b29137ac05222cbe4fedaf53ae3570445ce5eeea29f2e6fd0b5282708298767b76bcb2f7\n \n This makes it a bit clearer that the operation failed.\n] \n\n[D.UI.PatchHeader: define is_badname in terms of just_a_badname\nBen Franksen <ben.franksen@online.de>**20201019082954\n Ignore-this: 720c9fb07128b1d53c2d2f15a9a95bb826a6d5f8a74fd1af2a267734c81b098e2d154908256ff053\n] \n\n[resolve issue2659: check for bad patch name after invoking editor, too\nBen Franksen <ben.franksen@online.de>**20201019082812\n Ignore-this: b257b93a7a048f7f74b2b2bad6dbeb92e62d68d8ffe4ff5d53436e0efc57a94629c0041fc24e5029\n] \n\n[add progress reporting to show dependencies command\nBen Franksen <ben.franksen@online.de>**20201019115005\n Ignore-this: df0ee0241971b85c3947b6851148ab785aa0bef6c9d60220f9f85c8fc40ea981939d77861c05c888\n] \n\n[improve internal documentation in D.UI.Commands.ShowDependencies\nBen Franksen <ben.franksen@online.de>**20201019093907\n Ignore-this: fa155aa343d7d461070ec633af1d658d01ecf082965992a3af8ee42268035ab2c9064281df5169ec\n \n This hopefully makes it clearer how the algorithm works.\n] \n\n[fix and improve help text for show dependencies\nBen Franksen <ben.franksen@online.de>**20201019084706\n Ignore-this: 4371e702bb927e68793879a8219b303c9fc1d0880cc53332b2bab073ce7dbfed423fd0c453c0e02d\n] \n\n[resolve issue2658: show dependencies should only show direct dependencies\nBen Franksen <ben.franksen@online.de>**20201017171057\n Ignore-this: 37282380bbe8a48412aeac9a7c61ff3f99db4ddee3494cf78477750d3fbb68b5fd88375439ce81f6\n \n The code was written with that goal in mind, I just botched the way the\n direct and indirect dependencies are updated when a new dependency is found.\n] \n\n[fix: make test for issue1956 succeed and no longer mark as failing\nBen Franksen <ben.franksen@online.de>**20201017083452\n Ignore-this: d702bf35ff7c5e66463543f087655ee95ecbb92e40c6844f2c0cbd90e8fbdb9e501d996e054751\n] \n\n[drop dependency on sandi and use base16-bytestring >= 1.0\nBen Franksen <ben.franksen@online.de>**20200918090300\n Ignore-this: f283ca1a743233b869b8f2afbd279b6096199a48b0b5a62b99ea300540ca7b36a251dba19d54b97c\n \n This was prompted by the announcement of base16-bytestring-1.0.0.0 which\n claims to give major performance improvements and a simpler API. As we use\n sandi only for base16 en/decoding and already depended on base16-bytestring\n in addition to that, this seemed like a logical step. It also turned out\n that the API of base16-bytestring fits our conventions better, in particular\n we can drop the separate pass that converts between upper and lower case,\n which should give us further performance improvement.\n] \n\n[improve the prompt when asking for a long comment\nBen Franksen <ben.franksen@online.de>**20200816084814\n Ignore-this: 902d58609b5c372889ebe2e7a51593a4bfc2383f6b7d24446643f4acf5454bf7511b8c7043d40792\n \n We now ask whether they want to \"add a\" long comment or, if a prior log\n exists, \"edit the\" long comment.\n] \n\n[resolve issue2654: amend --prompt-long-comment removes the long comment\nBen Franksen <ben.franksen@online.de>**20200816083927\n Ignore-this: 4d6cd4f31351b8dc8ad96efa5a683eda304c39cb3f5b6edd412b5c27934b5fc403da002f87296bc0\n] \n\n[two bugfixes in the PrimV1 shrinker\nBen Franksen <ben.franksen@online.de>**20200923103309\n Ignore-this: 4ee2f606fd8e671a350e28abcf6f17d95f4bd44d0711ee9838efd8b688fe571c82ac75a41031123e\n] \n\n[remove dependency on split package\nBen Franksen <ben.franksen@online.de>**20200824105752\n Ignore-this: 80dcf05048af624778cfbb21ab7da6298938dc0a8a32f640e5ab79ccdf54b978c3c19bc65d8a2ba4\n] \n\n[remove work-around for issue1824\nBen Franksen <ben.franksen@online.de>**20200824055549\n Ignore-this: b275df1f44c660b75c1dee801798d1a9bfe12aa401f279824ebfb38b54f9a34826b4c8748b759f04\n \n The underlying bug in ghc has been fixed a long time ago. Besides, the macro\n is no longer passed via command line but instead by including cabal_macros.h.\n] \n\n[resolve issue2655: PACKAGE_VERSION is not defined\nBen Franksen <ben.franksen@online.de>**20200824053526\n Ignore-this: de5897e7e0fb5b33338cf490cdf669886dbb3a60e66b73c6f6af5d4ddafd0ab178065f0f62016b14\n \n This happens only if darcs is build with the -fcurl flag. The patch adapts\n src/hscurl.hs to use CURRENT_PACKAGE_VERSION and include the definition from\n \"cabal_macros.h\".\n] \n\n[TAG 2.16.2\nBen Franksen <ben.franksen@online.de>**20200819210622\n Ignore-this: 8aeca92b4f3d72a38b97ea681f4f87ea9f13e1a0abb37954596cbc64754cdaf4202fe95d848e9764\n] \n\n[add changelog entry for 2.16.2\nBen Franksen <ben.franksen@online.de>**20200818145545\n Ignore-this: 4e8b7d69a85b18d4b9d31a0bddd395b5c5cd12e7f0e88de3a596aec82e82b87b8ddf9389fc72d10b\n] \n\n[remove shelly dependency\nBen Franksen <ben.franksen@online.de>**20200817160619\n Ignore-this: 71facec4d831cfb9de3e14d837223a4db6655cba90564f7443ba46bf6b945e4b8a94be5f1957747b\n \n Instead, we add shelly/src to the hs-source-dirs of our test suite. This\n avoids problems when 'cabal install' is run inside an unpacked source tar\n ball.\n] \n\n[release.sh: check that we can run cabal install in the unpacked sdist\nBen Franksen <ben.franksen@online.de>**20200817163035\n Ignore-this: 2ad7be2d5b181041e7c009468a3dbc7ecdce43823925059191f10b1dd6549f6ddf9b28ae953dedf9\n] \n\n[bump version to 2.16.2\nBen Franksen <ben.franksen@online.de>**20200817161018\n Ignore-this: fd5134e6e2f6bc21b3b4a105bba253eb442c1ca213221ee8982eba7b9183c1e52858c8ccc3db96b7\n] \n\n[rollback \"replace buildHook, haddockHook, and replHook with postConf\"\nBen Franksen <ben.franksen@online.de>**20200815132031\n Ignore-this: 3f8255d2a10baf9c9c7f4fea00a5970f799c6e7d7f7d8882b01a3b8451c529b2dc1e2f9df386397c\n \n This was a mistake: with this change the Version.hs module will not be\n re-built when the repository changes.\n] \n\n[work around cabal stupidity in Setup.hs\nBen Franksen <ben.franksen@online.de>**20200815121037\n Ignore-this: 6834dddda06e5567e28924c8b7e2a2fa5c0e7b6b3efb2fc194ed5d52e7b8fbaebaf58839b1c767c7\n \n Cabal insists that all files in extra-source-files must actually exist, even\n though only the cabal sdist command actually needs them.\n] \n\n[resolve issue2570: coalesceHunk should take arguments in the natural order\nBen Franksen <ben.franksen@online.de>**20200801115452\n Ignore-this: 5e1d5b06d47a14dd6afad38416dcca55166a3c672f9092076b1a3ade57182d3857157c234dc3cb4e\n] \n\n[add (succeeding) test for issue1956\nBen Franksen <ben.franksen@online.de>**20200801235035\n Ignore-this: cf250c50e7392962dbc836b3ef48354db47904fb430d510c9f037da24cdc4db43c74957f2bc4d998\n] \n\n[resolve issue1930: issue595_get_permissions.sh buggy\nBen Franksen <ben.franksen@online.de>**20200801161720\n Ignore-this: 5b47fdf3c1a71852df2bc19237ac5dad873cae4e5fbcaa9b3c7a5e2572669001ea446fc0163bf9a0\n] \n\n[add (succeeding) test for issue2549\nBen Franksen <ben.franksen@online.de>**20200801134645\n Ignore-this: 8cb2b60aa8edb2e4ee44c11bcdb2a65d9ecc74632199fc3c0736f20552acf4d6c021d0b893aec8d5\n] \n\n[add (succeeding) test for issue2353\nBen Franksen <ben.franksen@online.de>**20200731204122\n Ignore-this: 25fa218665ac95f342d3125402b4a1a10102795a5b95bbda3eecfabde5a3a83d14d21b812c4f2813\n] \n\n[TAG 2.16.1\nBen Franksen <ben.franksen@online.de>**20200814093257\n Ignore-this: b5957de98ad629b97483fd6bee8941e2871a58aac4c559d37921feda3e88f06c5a939f40820abf9f\n] \n"